Text.Value: Don't go, Isobel. He's too strong. He'll kill you.
If she makes it back before me - tell her I love her. And I'll see her soon.
He offered me more gold than Aylin's freedom is worth.
What did he offer you? Power? Gold?

EditorData.NodeContext: Suddenly cold. She realizes you betrayed Aylin

Text.Value: Are you sure you want to do this?
After all the trouble you went through to free her...
Gone? What do you mean gone?
Lorroakan was too strong. I barely escaped with my life.
We were defeated and fled. Aylin should be here, unless Lorroakan intercepted her along the way.
You're lying. I can't believe it. You helped him, didn't you?
But I'll leave that to Aylin. I'm sure she will enjoy dealing with you herself.
So I should just leave her there in that madman's hands? Absolutely not. Absolutely not. Not ever.

EditorData.NodeContext: Strong emotion. Before she leaves and runs off to save Aylin

Text.Value: Good luck.
She's gone.
You defeated the Apostle of Myrkul. You mean to tell me this Lorroakan was stronger than the god of necromancy?

EditorData.NodeContext: Her suspicions are growing; she's seething

Text.Value: What?! How can - how could some wizard overpower both of you?
Stronger? No. But a better negotiator? Definitely.
I need to get her out of there.
He must wield some kind of divine power - or perhaps demonic. Moonmaiden, help me! Not another.
Thank you. You've been a true friend. When we come back - and we will - I'll get to thank you properly for standing beside us both.
There you are. Where's Aylin?

EditorData.NodeContext: Relieved/ worried. She's expecting to see Aylin right behind you, but she doesn't

Text.Value: I should strike you down where you stand.
I won't abandon her. Not again. Never again.
Lorroakan is a rich man. I took advantage of that.
What? You're disgusting.

EditorData.NodeContext: Spits on the floor. This is unlike her but the player evoked the animal in her.

Text.Value: I have bad news, Isobel. Lorroakan bested her. She's trapped in another soul cage.
He must be. I barely escaped with my life.
She's not coming back. Lorroakan has her now. Forget her.

Synopsis: Dialog with Isobel who is still waiting on Nightsong from going to Ramazith's tower. She is not coming back because Lorroakan soul caged her. Isobel will leave camp in bad terms to rescue her.
